1.e4 Nf6 2.e5 Nd5 3.d4 d6 4.c4 Nb4? {This move cannot be recommended. It is essentially a cheap trap.} 5.Qa4+ N8c6 6.d5 b5 {After} (6...Bf5 7.Na3 dxe5 8.dxc6 Nxc6 9.Be3 { White is         simply a piece up.}) 7.cxb5 Nd4 {The trap. White is winning as long as he does not take on b4.} 8.Na3 {Black loses one of his knights.}  *

