1.e4 Nf6 2.e5 Nd5 3.d4 d6 4.c4 Nb6 5.f4 g5 {The Planinc gambit. Black wants to undermine the support of e5.} 6.Nc3 {The most flexible move.} 6...Bg7 7.Nf3 dxe5?! {After White's natural reply dxe5     the only way to make sense of the pawn on g5 is to play g4 and     transpose to 7.... g4 with} 8.fxe5 g4 (8...h6 9.c5 Nd5 10.Bc4 c6 11.Qb3 { gives White a clear advantage. Black loses a pawn unless he plays the awful-looking e6.}) 9.Nh4 c5 10.d5 {This transposes to  7...g4  (variation:9119349)  .}  *

