1.e4 Nf6 2.e5 Nd5 3.d4 d6 4.c4 Nb6 5.f4 g5 {The Planinc gambit. Black wants to undermine the support of e5.} 6.Nc3 {The most flexible move.} 6...Bg7 7.Nf3 Bg4 8.h3 {the simplest move. Since retreating     to f5 or h5 runs into g4 Black has to take on f3.} 8...Bxf3 9.Qxf3 dxe5 10.dxe5 Nc6 (10...gxf4 11.c5 { White wins a piece.} 11...N6d7 12.Qxb7 { +-}) 11.g3 {Keeping Black's dark-squared bishop out of the game.} 11...gxf4 12.gxf4 Nd4 13.Qe4 f5 14.Qd3 e6 15.Be3± {The bishop pair, the space advantage and the fact that both the knight on b6 and the bishop on g7 are currently not doing anything give White a clear advantage.}  *

