1.e4 Nf6 2.e5 Nd5 3.d4 d6 4.c4 Nb6 5.f4 g5 {The Planinc gambit. Black wants to undermine the support of e5.} 6.Nc3 {The most flexible move.} 6...Bg7 7.Nf3 gxf4 8.Bxf4 Nc6 {still the best move in a difficult situation.} 9.exd6 {White's idea is simple. Take on d6 to give Black no targets for counterplay in the center. Then play Qd2, O-O-O and Bh6 after which the dark squares on Black's kingside will be seriously weakened.} (9.c5 { Is another good line for White.} 9...dxc5 10.dxc5 Qxd1+ 11.Rxd1 Nd7 { Now White's pawns look overextended but counterattacking c7 gives White an advantage.} 12.Nd5 O-O (12...Kd8 ? 13.e6 { +-}) 13.Nxc7 Rb8 14.e6 Nxc5 15.exf7+ Rxf7 16.Bc4 e6 17.g3) 9...cxd6 10.Qd2 O-O 11.Bh6 {Threatening Qg5.} 11...Bxh6 12.Qxh6 e5 13.O-O-O Qe7 14.d5 Nb4 15.g4! {Anticipating f5.} 15...f5 {Otherwise White gets a crushing attack with Rg1, Nh4-f5.} 16.g5 {followed by g6 and Rg1 with a strong attack.}  *

