1.e4 Nf6 2.e5 Nd5 3.d4 d6 4.c4 Nb6 5.f4 dxe5 6.fxe5 c5 {Black attacks White's center immediately. If White would let Black     play cxd4 then defending the pawn on e5 could become a problem for     White.} 7.d5 {avoiding the exchange and also preventing Nc6.} 7...e6 {Black now uses d5 as a new target.} 8.Nc3 exd5 9.cxd5 {The starting point of this line. If Black can develop his pieces,     especially the bishop on f8, then the pawns on e5 and d5 may become     difficult to defend. If on the other hand White manages to prevent     Black from developing for long enough then the extra space may be used     for starting an attack.} 9...c4 {Black wants to put more pressure on White's center with Bb4 or target     White's dark squares on the kingside with Bc5.} 10.d6 {The key move. White is much better now because Black cannot break up     White's dominating pawns in the center. White's plan is     straightforward: complete development with Bf4, Nf3 and Be2. If Black     attacks the center too early with f6 then Nb5 with the threat Nc7+ is     strong.} 10...Nc6 (10...Be6 11.Nf3 Nc6 12.Bf4 { transposes to the  mainline  (variation:9119503/#/12/w)}) 11.Bf4 {In this position Black can try to break up White's pawns on e5 and d6 with f6 or fianchetto his dark-squared bishop with h6 and g5.} 11...f6 {Black tries to break down White's center     immediately.} 12.Nb5 fxe5 13.Be3 {The bishop eyes the knight on b6. If Black plays a6 then the knight on b6 will be hanging after the intermediate check Nc7+. With that being said, Bg3 is also quite good.} 13...Bf5 14.Nf3 {The simplest solution. White simply completes         his development.} (14.Nc7+ Kd7 15.Nf3 Bxd6 16.Nxa8 Qxa8 17.Rc1 { is             good as well but more complicated.}) 14...Rc8 (14...a6 ? 15.Nc7+ { and Bxb6.}) 15.Be2 a6 16.Nc7+ Rxc7 17.dxc7 Qxc7 18.O-O± {Black has two pawns for the exchange but the pawn on c4 will likely fall soon and it is not so easy for Black to get his king to safety.} 18...Be7 {Black has to hurry with getting his king to safety because otherwise it will be stuck in the center after Kh1, Bxb6 and Bxc4.} 19.Kh1 O-O 20.Bxb6 Qxb6 21.Qd5+ Kh8 22.Nxe5 {and Black has not enough compensation for the exchange.}  *

