1.e4 Nf6 {The Alekhine defence was introduced by Alexander Alekhine almost 100 years ago. Black allows White to gain several tempi attacking by advancing pawns to attack the knight. Black plans to regain the lost tempi by forcing White to first defend and later exchange these pawns. Once Black succeeds in doing this he may be able to exploit the weakened squares in the center which White can no longer defend with pawns. White on the other hand can try to use his space advantage to start an attack     and also to make use of Black's misplaced knight on b6.} 2.e5 Ne4?! {A move which has been played occasionally in the     pre-engine area. White wins a pawn or forces Black to weaken his     kingside considerably with} 3.d4 {threatening to trap the knight with     f3.} 3...e6 {Black protects g5 to prepare the retreat Ng5 and also     prevents f3 with the threat Qh4.} (3...f6 { keeps the pawn but gives White an impressive         center after} 4.Nh3 d5 5.f3 Bxh3 6.fxe4 Be6 7.c4 {.}) 4.Nh3! {renewing the threat f3.} 4...h6 5.Qg4 d5 6.f3 {and White     will win a pawn after Black plays Ng5.}  *

[Event "Quickstarter 2"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "?"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]

1.e4 Nf6 {The Alekhine defence was introduced by Alexander Alekhine almost 100 years ago. Black allows White to gain several tempi attacking by advancing pawns to attack the knight. Black plans to regain the lost tempi by forcing White to first defend and later exchange these pawns. Once Black succeeds in doing this he may be able to exploit the weakened squares in the center which White can no longer defend with pawns. White on the other hand can try to use his space advantage to start an attack     and also to make use of Black's misplaced knight on b6.} 2.e5 Ng8 {This rare move has been played occasionally also by strong     players but it gives White a small advantage without risk.} 3.d4 d6 4.f4 (4.Nf3 { is of course good as well.}) 4...Bf5 5.Bd3 {leaves White with a stable center and a space     advantage. That the c-pawn is still on c2 makes defending the center     much easier because the pawn on d4 can be defended with c2-c3 if     necessary.} (5.Nf3 { followed by Bd3 is just as good.})  *

