1.e4 Nf6 {The Alekhine defence was introduced by Alexander Alekhine almost 100 years ago. Black allows White to gain several tempi attacking by advancing pawns to attack the knight. Black plans to regain the lost tempi by forcing White to first defend and later exchange these pawns. Once Black succeeds in doing this he may be able to exploit the weakened squares in the center which White can no longer defend with pawns. White on the other hand can try to use his space advantage to start an attack     and also to make use of Black's misplaced knight on b6.} 2.e5 Nd5 3.d4 Nb6 {Black wants to see White's next move before committing his     d-pawn to d6 or d5.} 4.c4 {The simplest choice.} 4...d6 {Black has     nothing better.} 5.f4 {and we have transposed back to the mainline.}  *

[Event "Quickstarter 4"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
