th the threats Ne7 and Nc7 give more than  enough compensation.} 18...Nc4 {Black wants to take on e5 with the  knight on c4 and use the knight on d7 to block the passed pawn. But this  removes the protection from the square d5 and now Nd5 is an even stronger  threat,} 19.Qc2 {Almost all reasonable queen moves are good. I chose Qc2  because I think it is the simplest option.} 19...Ncxe5 (19...Ndxe5 20.Rxe5 { If bishop or rook take on e5 then d7 wins      and if the knight takes then Nxe5 followed by d7 wins.}) 20.Nd5 Nxf3 21.gxf3 Rxe1 22.Rxe1 {Black's extra pawn does not matter.  White threatens Ne7+, Re7 and Nc7.}  *

