1.e4 Nf6 2.e5 Nd5 3.d4 d6 4.c4 Nb6 5.f4 dxe5 6.fxe5 Nc6 7.Be3 Bf5 8.Nc3 e6 9.Nf3 Nb4 (9...Be7 10.Be2 Nb4 11.Rc1 c5 { transposes to the mainline.}) 10.Rc1 c5 11.Be2 (11.Qb3 { The engine's suggestion. It may be even stronger     than the main line with 11. Be2. The idea is to take on c5 and then     play Qxb4. But Black can avoid this line by starting with 9...Be7     before playing Nb4 and c5.}) (11.d5 { does not work} 11...exd5 12.a3 d4 { ∓}) 11...Be7 12.a3 cxd4 {The only move. Both} (12...Na6 13.d5) { and} (12...Nc6 13.d5 Nd4 14.Nxd4 cxd4 15.Qxd4) { are hopeless for Black.} 13.Nxd4 Na6 14.b4 (14.Nxf5 exf5 15.b4 { is also much better for White.}) 14...Bg6 {After other moves White is winning after Nxf5, possibly O-O, and c5-c6 making use of the overloaded pawn on b7.} 15.c5 Nd5 16.Bb5+ (16.Qa4+ Kf8 17.Nxd5 Qxd5 18.O-O { is winning as well.}) 16...Kf8 17.Nxe6+ {The most forcing continuation.} 17...fxe6 18.Nxd5 Qxd5 19.O-O+ Kg8 (19...Bf5 20.Rxf5+ exf5 21.Qxd5 { wins immediately.}) 20.Bc4 Qxe5 (20...Qxd1 21.Bxe6+ Bf7 22.Bxf7+ Kf8 23.Rcxd1 { also wins.}) 21.Bd4 Qe4 22.Re1 {White wins because Black cannot protect e6 any longer.}  *

