1.-- {This is my current repertoire against the Alekhine defense. I played the Four Pawns Attack for several years as a junior player until a number of stronger Alekhine players convinced me that 4. Nf3 is the way to go. 

Recently I was considering to start playing the Alekhine defense as Black. I was happy with what I found against 4. Nf3 but surprisingly I could not find a clear path to equality against the Four Pawns Attack. This repertoire is the result of my failed attempts to find a good answer to the Four Pawns Attack. 

My suggested way of studying is:  
1  Do the quickstarter.
2  Read the introduction to chapters you are interested in. 
3  Learn those chapters. 
4  Go to 2  (if you still have energy)  .
X  Consult the move order guide whenever necessary.
Y  Do the puzzles at the end of the course if you are curious what I consider to be the 10 most important positions in this course. Don't just try to remember the correct move but try to recall all the necessary variations and the underlying reasons given.}  *

