[FEN "3rkb1r/pppq1ppp/1nn1p3/4P3/2PP2b1/2N1BN2/PP2B1PP/R2Q1RK1 w k - 6 12"]

{How should White deal with the threat Bxf3 and Nxd4  (or Nxc4 in case White recaptures with the bishop on f3?)} 12.b3! {Here I believe the best move is this rarely played move.The idea is to secure c4 to keep the knight on b6 out of the game for a while and to also allow the bishop on e2 to recapture on f3 in case of Bxf3. This protects the pawn on d4 at least for the moment because Bxf3 and Nxd4 can be answered with Bxf3 and Bxb7. White's standard moves in this position do not give White more than perhaps a small advantage.} (12.d5 Bxf3 13.Bxf3 Nxe5 14.c5 Nxd5 15.Nxd5 exd5 16.Bd4 { with compensation for the pawns but probably not more.}) (12.c5 Nd5 13.Nxd5 Qxd5 14.Ng5 Bxe2 15.Qxe2 Rd7 16.Qf2 { with a small advantage for White.}) (12.Ng5 Nxc4 13.Rxf7 Nxe3 14.Rxd7 Nxd1 15.Rxd8+ Nxd8 16.Bxg4 { with an equal endgame.}) { For details click  here  (variation:9119626/#/12/w)  .} 12...Bb4 {Preparing to castle with tempo.} (12...Be7 13.Qe1 Bxf3 { after other moves White can secure d4 with Rad1.} 14.Bxf3 Nxd4 15.Bxb7 { is better for White.}) 13.Ne4 O-O {After} (13...Bxf3 14.Bxf3 Nxd4 { Black wins a pawn but White gets more than enough compensation after} 15.Bh5 { Note that g6 is impossible here because of the fork on f6.}) 14.Kh1 {Sooner or later necessary to avoid unpleasant checks on d4.} 14...Be7 {If Black takes the pawn with Bxf3 and Nxd4 then White gets a strong attack similar to the mainline.} 15.Qe1 Bxf3 16.Rxf3 Nxd4 17.Rh3 {With a strong attack for White.}  *

[Event "Key position 05 (answer)"]
[Site "?"]
