{Should White play a3 or is there a better move?} 14.Bc1! {White threatens to trap the bishop with Nb1 or Na4 followed by a3.} (14.a3 Bxc3 15.bxc3 h6 { followed by b6 gives Black counterplay.}) { For details click  here  (variation:9119667/#/14/w)  .} 14...Bxc3 15.bxc3 {White is better. The key difference is that Black's attempt to create counterplay with b6 can now be answered with Ba3 preserving White's pawn structure.}  *

