{How should White develop his pieces?} 9.Bf4 {White postpones the development of the knight on g1 until the Black's light-squared bishop has moved to avoid the pin Bg4 or at least to win a tempo.  For details click  here  (variation:9285188/#/9/w)} 9...O-O 10.Qd2 {White still postpones Nf3 and prepares to castle queenside.} 10...e6 11.O-O-O exd5 12.cxd5 {White is better. See the chapter on 6...c5 and g6 for details.}  *

