{How should White continue?} 8.Rc1! {Since the pawn on c4 is indirectly defended by the queen check on a4 White does not have to play b3 just yet. Once b3 has been played Rc1 or Qd2 will almost certainly become necessary to protect the knight on c3 because after c5 by Black it will be difficult to keep the long diagonal closed. The point of this move order is to play b3 only after Black has castled and the pawn on c4 is no longer  (indirectly)  protected. The upshot is that Black's counterplay in the center is delayed by one move because Black has to castle to 'force' White to play b3.} (8.d5 Bc8 { White still has a small advantage but Black can destroy White's center with dxe5, c6 and cxd5.}) (8.b3 { Fairly popular but a minor inaccuracy in my opinion. Black can attack the center immediately without castling with} 8...dxe5 9.fxe5 c5 10.d5 Bf5 { In comparison to the 'correct' answer 8. Rc1 the moves Rc1 by White and O-O by Black are missing. This difference is in Black's favor since the knight on c3 is undefended here.}) { For details click  here  (variation:9119473/#/8/w)  .} 8...O-O {Taking on c4 gives White an advantage whether or not Black captures on e5 first:} (8...Nxc4 9.Qa4+ Qd7 { the tactics after} (9...b5 10.Nxb5 Nxe3 11.Nxc7+ { are also in White's favor.} 10.Bxc4 { Qxa4  11.Nxa4} Bxc4 { 12.Rxc4  b5  13.Rxc7  with a nice endgame for White, or}) (8...dxe5 9.fxe5 Nxc4 10.Bxc4 Bxc4 11.Qa4+ b5 12.Nxb5 Bxb5 13.Qxb5+ Nd7 14.Nf3 Rb8 15.Qe2 Nb6 16.O-O { leads to a small but definite advantage for White. Black's pawns and light squares on the queenside are very weak. Doubling the rooks on the c-file with Rc5 and Rfc1 in combination with Qa6, Qc4 or Ra5 will very likely win a pawn in the long run.})) 9.b3 dxe5 10.fxe5 c5 11.d5 Bf5 (11...Bc8 12.Nf3 Bg4 13.Bxc5 { is also better for White.}) 12.Be2 {White prevents Nd7 with this move because g4 would trap the bishop if there is a knight on d7.} 12...Bxe5 13.Nf3 Bd6 14.O-O {White has more than enough compensation for the pawn. Black has not complete his development yet and White can already start attacking with Bh6 and Ng5.}  *

