{How should White continue?} 8.c5! {White gains more space and more importantly stabilizes the center because Black's main attacking idea, the move c5, is no longer possible.} (8.Be3 { allows Black to destroy White's center.} 8...c5 9.dxc5 N6d7 { White may still be a bit better after} 10.e6 { but I do not like White's position.}) { For details click  here  (variation:9119458/#/8/w)  .} 8...Nd5 (8...N6d7 9.Bc4 O-O 10.Nf3 Nc6 11.O-O { White is clearly better. There is no easy way for Black to untangle the minor pieces on the queenside.}) 9.Bc4 Be6 (9...e6 10.Nf3 { White can continue with Bg5, Ne4 and O-O. White is better.}) 10.Qb3 Nxc3 11.Bxe6 fxe6 12.bxc3 Qd5 13.Nf3 {White is better. O-O and Ng5 are next.}  *

