1.e4 Nf6 2.e5 Nd5 3.d4 d6 4.c4 Nb6 5.f4 Bf5 6.Nc3 e6 7.Nf3 dxe5 8.fxe5 Bb4 9.Bd3 (9.a3 Bxc3+ 10.bxc3 { is the repertoire  recommendation  (variation:9119342/#/10/w)  (.)}) 9...c5 (9...Bxd3 10.Qxd3 { Here White can continue with O-O, Ne4, b3 and Bb2      and a clear advantage.}) 10.Bxf5 exf5 11.Bg5 (11.d5 { This is probably even stronger than Bg5. White sacrifices a pawn for a strong pawn center.} 11...Nxc4 12.O-O O-O (12...Bxc3 13.bxc3 Nb6 14.c4 { is much better for White.}) 13.Qb3 Bxc3 (13...Na5 14.Qc2 Bxc3 15.Qxc3 b6 16.Rd1 { followed by Bf4. The pawn on f5 is difficult to defend because after g6 the dark squares around Black's king will be very weak.}) 14.Qxc4 Bd4+ 15.Nxd4 cxd4 16.Rxf5 { White will pick up d4 in a few moves with a good position and an extra pawn.}) 11...Qd7 12.O-O (12.d5 { can transpose to the game. Here, just as in the game, Black should take on c3 before taking on c4. For      instance,} 12...Bxc3+ 13.bxc3 O-O 14.Qd3 Qa4 15.O-O Qxc4 16.Qxf5 { White has a dangerous attack after e6 or Be7 and Ng5.}) 12...O-O 13.d5 Nxc4 {Taking on c3 first was better. But after} (13...Bxc3 14.bxc3 Nxc4 15.Qd3 { followed by Rae1 White still has a much better position.}) 14.Qe2 Bxc3 15.Qxc4 {This move is the reason why Black should have taken on c3 one move      earlier. Now Black wins the pawn on b2 as well but loses too much time     in the process.} 15...Bxb2 16.Rab1 Bd4+ 17.Nxd4 cxd4 18.e6 fxe6 19.dxe6 Qc8 20.Qd5 Qc6 21.Qxd4 (21.Qb3 { was strongest} 21...Kh8 (21...Re8 22.Rxf5 { White is threatening e7+ and Rf8+.} 22...Qb6 23.Rb5 Qd6 24.e7+ Kh8 25.Qf7 Nc6 26.Rf1 { White's threats 27.Rd5          and 28. Rd8, and 27.Bf6 gxf6 28. Rh5 decide the game.}) 22.Rfc1 Qa6 23.Qxb7 Qxb7 24.Rxb7 { and the threats Rcc7 and Bf4-e5      decide the game.}) 21...Qxe6 22.Rxb7 Qg6 (22...Rf7 23.Qd8+ Rf8 24.Qc7 Qg6 25.Be7 Re8 26.Bd6 { and Black is      almost in zugzwang.} 26...Na6 { does not work because White has} 27.Qc4+ Kh8 28.Qxa6 { picking up the knight.}) 23.Bc1 Nc6 24.Qd5+ Kh8 25.Bb2 Rad8 26.Rxg7 Rxd5 27.Rxg6+ Nd4 28.Rg4 {The pawn on f5 is pinned and now the pinned knight on d4 is lost.}  1-0

[Event "AUT North-ch"]
